    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.5-7_0001" />

                <note type="curatorial">A8 Neihardt Collection</note> 
                <fw type="curatorial">5</fw>

                <opener>
                                    <dateline>River Landing, Bismarck Aug 28th 1915</dateline>

                <salute>Dear Mr Neihardt</salute></opener> <p>i<sic>I</sic> received your letter yesterday with <unclear>lavender for which</unclear> I thank you for both i<sic>I</sic> note all you say with interest and pleasure i<sic>I</sic> will tell you about the trip when i<sic>I</sic> tried to make the trip i<sic>I</sic> was to have a man that works <unclear>for</unclear> <unclear/> <unclear>Baker</unclear> to help me <unclear>as it was the</unclear> <unclear/> to take the mess with <unclear/> as a <unclear>piket</unclear> when i<sic>I</sic> arrived at Williston i<sic>I</sic> found they did not have the man that they agreed to here but one that i<sic>I</sic> did not want instead so i<sic>I</sic> told them that i<sic>I</sic> would go to Bismarck and no further so i<sic>I</sic> left the <unclear>Boats</unclear> here i<sic>I</sic> assure <add>you</add> it would have given me pleasure to have had you on a trip of that kind it turned out <unclear>they only went</unclear> to Sioux City where they are now</p>

                <p>There is three <unclear>Snow Boats</unclear> on the River one works Bet<unclear/> 
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.5-7_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">6</fw>
                    
                    Kansas City one between Kansas City &amp; Sioux City the other Between Sioux City &amp; Yellow Stone<sic>Yellowstone</sic> River</p>
                
                <p>the engineer in Charge has his head quarters<sic>headquarters</sic> in Kansas City. i<sic>I</sic> Believe you Could <unclear>get authority</unclear> to make one <unclear>or all</unclear> of all these trips in <unclear>verity</unclear> him it would Be well to state that of course you would <unclear>expect to pay</unclear> your Board of Course he would Charge you nothing should i<sic>I</sic> know of a <unclear>Boat</unclear> going to make <unclear>such</unclear> a trip i<sic>I</sic> will <unclear>notify</unclear> you with pleasure also do all i<sic>I</sic> can to assist you in getting by it. i<sic>I</sic> will send you a picture Next Week will i<sic>I</sic> expect one in return of you &amp; your Wife <unclear>i<sic>I</sic> here at time look selective of siotu</unclear> of Famous men &amp; women who has sent them to <unclear>new hara.</unclear> Splendid <unclear>Cup</unclear> this <unclear>seasons</unclear> all of Scott Baker <unclear>Boats</unclear> will be <unclear>Running</unclear> soon <unclear>as</unclear></p> 
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.5-7_0003"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                    
                <p>With Best wishes for your Health and Happiness</p>
                <closer>
                                <salute>Sincerely your friend</salute>
                    
                                <signed>Grant P. Marsh</signed>
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
